             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a constable; I and Mansfield stopped the two prisoners going to sell these things at an old iron shop in Bowl-yard, St. Giles's; it was about ten at night, on the 20th instant; they said they could not tell what was in the bundle, they had just found them; they have been in my possession ever since.</p>
               <p>(Produced and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER M'GINNIS's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I know no more of the things, than the dead in the grave; I was in liquor, and enquiring for a lodging.</p>
               <p>PRISONER CAPON's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I found the things.</p>
