               <p>Court to Jury. Gentlemen, this is exactly the same as the last case; you see the consequence of going by so uncertain a rule, or no rule at all. It is much safer to adhere to the rule of law, because then you have a certain guide by which to direct your verdict; then magistrates will know on what grounds they ought to commit; and prosecutors will know on what grounds they can support a prosecution.</p>
               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. Justice HEATH.</p>
